comments.text: Honestly, after watching a few on this subject I feel so sad. Of course, this is one of the more 'fun' videos because of the cringe, but reality is daunting😥. Companies like Palantir & OpenAI are developing scary things and I am scared that AI is extensively going to be used to monitor and control citizens. The moment is here where AI is going to make decisions on you being a fraud or not getting coverage for healthcare etc. I am wondering what I personally can do to raise awareness and stop AI from eventually being integrated in all government and insurance companies. As I said before, the easiest thing I can think of is telling people that ditching the use of big-tech in your life is still easy. Buy a Linux phone, use alternative app stores and open-source software. It luckily still is really easy to protect your freedom and privacy online. Try to think for yourself for example when writing a letter or report, it gets easier and in my experience it is much more rewarding to be the best writer of your class even when they kill your internet connection and only give you a pencil and paper. The more difficult thing is choosing the right political party to vote for, if that is even possible in your country.... 😟I guess the biggest power I have is not letting them make any profit on me. Now I just want to unplug everything and play a vinyl record.... phone off, computer off, TV unplugged. Thanks for your videos, with love💛
